## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: Latest

After reading excel file and make a duplicate of row, the duplicated row cannot merged cells

## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

// initilaize exceljs

const workbook = new exceljs.Workbook();

workbook.xlsx.readFile(path.join(__dirname, "path of excel file"))
.then(dat => {
        // get the worksheet
        let worksheet = workbook.getWorksheet(1);
        worksheet.duplicateRow(1, 1, true);
        worksheet.mergeCells("A2:C2");
});

## The expected behaviour:

<!-- A clear and concise description of what you expected to happen. -->

The error stated that cannot merge cells because its already merged.

